            <title>[SOLR-9768] RecordingJsonParser produces incomplete json when updated document stream is larger than input parser&apos;s buffer size</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-9768</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While using srcField, RecordingJsonParser produce incomplete json when updated document stream is larger than buffer size (8192). &lt;br/&gt;
Fast fix is to align all documents in stream to buffer size. Another is attached in patch bellow.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
